<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Manchester City have opened talks with Benfica over a £50million deal for defender Ruben Dias.</p>

<p>The Premier League title contenders have switched to the stylish 23-year-old after growing frustrated by Sevilla's valuation of Jules Kounde.</p>

<p>Dias has long been on their shortlist but had been priced at £87million owing to his buy out clause.</p>

<p>Manchester City have opened talks with Benfica over a £50million deal for Ruben Dias</p>

<p>Dias has been on their shortlist but had been priced at £87million due to his buy out clause</p>

<p>The knock-on effects of the covid pandemic though mean Benfica are now willing to drop their price to attract much needed revenue.</p>

<p>City may also include Nicolas Otamendi in negotiations but Benfica would prefer a straight cash deal at this stage.</p>

<p>Dias has a long-term contract until the summer of 2024 at the Portuguese side.</p>

<p>Guardiola is an admirer of the Portugal international, who made 49 appearances across all competitions for club and country last season. </p>

<p>City may also include Nicolas Otamendi in negotiations but Benfica prefer straight cash</p>

<p>City have become frustrated by Sevilla's valuation of Jules Kounde and have now moved on</p>
